The Faculty of Engineering Alumni Association, University of Lagos will on Saturday March 24, 2018, hold its 2nd Alumni Lecture at the Julius Berger Lecture Theatre of the faculty. The lecture, titled ‘Alumni Association: A Veritable Tool for Networking and Promotion of Professionalism’, will be delivered by Engineer Dideolu Falobi, Managing Director, Kresta Laurel Limited, Lagos. According to a statement signed by the Chairman, board of trustees of the association, Engr Oye Eribake, the event, which starts at 11am, will also feature the Inauguration of the Faculty of Engineering ‘Industry Advisory Board’ (FE-IAB) and the Annual General Meeting, where new executive members of the alumni association will be elected. The statement said the association was inaugurated on March 16, 2017 as a veritable tool for the development of the faculty and a platform for social interaction and networking among the alumni.